<h1>Tip Catalogue</h1>
<h2>Technology and Innovation for Daily Life</h2>
<p>People with Parkinson’s face unique challenges on a daily basis. Cell phone buttons are too small, holding a camera steady isn't always realistic, and shirt buttons are unnecessarily tricky. But we want you to be able to complete ordinary functions with ease, pursue all of your hobbies and succeed at the workplace. </p>
<p>So consider this an index of daily challenges faced by people with Parkinson's. Underneath each challenge is a list of potential solutions, apps, and innovations that have been tested and recommended by others in the PD community. </p>
<p>This is a curated, crowd-sourced page, meaning that you can contribute your ideas or share your challenges. Check out the widget on the right to submit.</p>
<p></p>
<div class="info-bar orange">
<h3 id="donations" class="info-bar-l"><span class="faqCatChild">Technology</span><a name="donations" href="javascript:void(0);"></a></h3>
<p class="info-bar-r"><a href="javascript:void(0)" id="handletoggle1" class="ko bold" onclick="toggleAllNLevel('1'); ">OPEN All</a>&gt;</p>
<div class="clearit"> </div>
</div>
<div id="subcat1" class="subcat">
<div id="info-hdr1-1" class="info-hdr">
<p class="info-hdr-2"><img src="https://www.michaeljfox.org/images/icon-open-info.gif" alt="" style="float: left;" width="18" height="18" /><strong>    The buttons on my phone, tablet, or computer are too small.</strong></p>
<div class="clearit"> </div>
</div>
<div id="info-info1-1" class="info-info" style="display: none;"><img src="/files/social-media-icons-2011-dec-55.jpg;" />
<p><b>Potential Solutions:<b></b></b></p>
<p>Many people with Parkinson's disease have given up on smartphones because the buttons are simply too small. Uncontrollable movements make navigating a tiny screen nearly impossible. However, the latest technology is actually helping smartphones live up to their name--so much so, that we actually would recommend a smartphone over a landline. Here’s why:</p>
<br />
<p>There are numerous button-enlarging and voice-activated apps for both Android and Apple devices. Apps are essentially small pieces of software that you can download to your phone within minutes. Many of these apps also come with voice-activated dialing (say, “Call Johnny” to your phone, and it will dial him for you). You might also receive vibration, noise and visual feedback when you’ve hit buttons, so that you can be sure you’ve hit your target.</p>
<br />
<p><b>Related Technology</b>:</p>
<br />
<ul>
<li>Samsung Easy Mode</li>
<li>Big Buttons Keyboard App (Android) FREE</li>
<li>Siri (iPhone) FREE</li>
<li>Samsung Galaxy cellphone</li>
<li>Mountain Focus IS</li>
<li>Big Keys</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
