<div id="subcat1" class="subcat">
<div id="info-hdr2-1" class="info-hdr">
<p class="info-hdr-2"><img src="https://www.michaeljfox.org/images/icon-open-info.gif" alt="" width="18" height="18" /> <strong>  It's difficult to turn pages while reading books, music, or any document.</strong></p>
<div class="clearit"></div>
</div>
<div id="info-info2-1" class="info-info" style="display: none;">
<p>A Parkinson’s diagnosis can hinder your daily work routine and favorite hobbies when dexterity transforms the act of turning pages into a major problem. A Parkinson’s patient recently posted on our Facebook, “I am a classical organist and conductor...and early on in dealing with the disease, page turning was my great failure!”</p>
<br />
<p>Some phones have built-in software that can help. The Samsung 4s cellphone, for example, responds to hand swipes in addition to touch, so that you can simply wave your hand across the screen to turn the page on your Kindle App.</p>
<br />
<p><b>Related Technology</b>:</p>
<br />
<ul>
<li>ForScore</li>
<li>Airturn</li>
<li>Kindle</li>
</ul>
</div>
